content.description:
This route overhangs more than you'd suspect standing at the bottom. Drilled bolt ladder style from the ground. There are 2 cruxes: one in the middle and one up top, both require sequence, although at least one brute has pulled through using pure muscle.. It has really cool crystal lined pockets on it too, some sharper than others.

It is plagued by the same dust skin as it's neighbor.
content.location: This is the far left route. There is an uncompleted project in between this and In my Heel.

content.description:
80m rope required to lower the whole way!! Has "mid-point" lowering chains to the right, in between routes, for shorter ropes. !!!!!!!!!TIE A KNOT IN THE END OF YOUR ROPE!!!!!!!!! if you will be belayed to the mid chains, and have belayer untie end if you will be pulling the rope.

The bottom 1/3 consists of mostly long fun moves on good grips while grazing past less than appealing landscape. Pockets lined with crystal and hidden holes abound. A good rest is found easily before trending right, and into the better looking landscape with more hidden holes and pockets. The thin crux awaits way up on the vertical headwall, and spits you into a shallow alcove, under a big rotted crystal area. Now you get to take in the reality of the altitude gained before doing a two bolt long boulder that renders the chains.
content.protection: 17- 1/2"x7" bolts w/fixed draws and chain anchor/belay
content.location: When you walk up the hill towards the cave, you can see the start almost straight ahead, maybe slightly to the left.

content.description: More pretty crystals in pockets. Maybe the crux is in the dihedral thing or maybe it's deciding which hand to put in which pocket. Either way it's a fun ride.
content.protection: Bolts. Chain at top anchors. All stainless
content.location: Left side of the wall. Start is at the right side of the top terrace. The tree seems to be pointing at the chains.

climbs.name: In My Heel
climbs.fa: James Garrett and Jon Allen, July 1994

content.description: The crux is high. It was dirty, but reports now indicate it has cleaned up considerably. Lots of pockets and interesting sequential moves.
content.protection: QDs to a two bolt belay. Drilled on lead with a Ryobi from hooks and gear. Has cleaned up alot since the time of the FA.
content.location: This is the first route located on the right as you enter the Narrows of South Willow Canyon. Go up and under a huge hanging cottonwood stump to wall with a huge cave at its base. IN MY HEEL traverses across the top of the cave to the first bolt and continues up past others to the chains. This is the first sizeable piece of rock as one enters the narrows on the right side of the road going up canyon. It has seen many repeats from the local crowd over the years, but is being reported now for the first time.
